## INTERVIEW PROCESS FRAMEWORK

### Standard Interview Framework (All Roles)

#### Stage 1: Application Screening (1-2 days)
**Checklist**:
- [ ] Meets minimum qualifications
- [ ] Resume quality and presentation
- [ ] Portfolio/work samples (for relevant roles)
- [ ] Cover letter demonstrates genuine interest
- [ ] No major red flags in employment history

#### Stage 2: Phone/Video Screening (30 minutes)
**Interviewer**: Hiring Manager or HR
**Goals**: 
- Confirm basic qualifications
- Assess communication skills  
- Gauge interest and cultural fit
- Explain role and company
- Screen for salary expectations

**Sample Questions**:
- "Walk me through your background and what brought you here"
- "What interests you about our company/mission?"
- "Describe your ideal work environment"
- "What are your salary expectations?"
- "When could you start if selected?"

#### Stage 3: Skills Assessment (varies by role)
**Technical Roles**: Coding challenge or technical test
**Design Roles**: Portfolio review + design challenge
**Sales/Marketing**: Case study or presentation
**Operations**: Process improvement case study

**Guidelines**:
- Time limit: 2-4 hours maximum
- Real-world, job-relevant scenarios
- Clear evaluation criteria
- Feedback provided to all candidates

#### Stage 4: Technical/Functional Interview (60-90 minutes)
**Technical Roles**: Code review + system design + problem solving
**Non-Technical Roles**: Case studies + situational questions + role-specific skills

**Interview Structure**:
- 10 minutes: Warm-up and role overview
- 30 minutes: Technical/functional assessment  
- 30 minutes: Problem-solving scenarios
- 10 minutes: Candidate questions
- 10 minutes: Next steps discussion

#### Stage 5: Cultural Fit Interview (45 minutes)
**Interviewer**: Founder or senior team member
**Goals**:
- Assess alignment with company values
- Evaluate teamwork and collaboration style
- Understand motivation and career goals
- Present company vision and growth plans

**Sample Questions**:
- "Describe a time you had to work with a difficult team member"
- "How do you handle ambiguity and changing priorities?"
- "What motivates you in your work?"
- "Where do you see yourself in 3-5 years?"
- "What questions do you have about our company culture?"

#### Stage 6: Reference Checks (2-3 references)
**Reference Questions**:
- "What were [Candidate]'s primary responsibilities?"
- "How would you rate their performance? Top 10%? 25%?"
- "What were their biggest strengths and areas for improvement?"
- "How did they handle feedback and coaching?"
- "Would you hire them again? Why or why not?"

#### Stage 7: Offer Discussion
**Components**:
- Salary negotiation
- Equity explanation and vesting schedule  
- Benefits overview
- Start date coordination
- Onboarding plan overview

### Role-Specific Interview Modifications

#### Engineering Roles
- **Technical Challenge**: 2-4 hour take-home assignment
- **Code Review**: Review their solution with them
- **System Design**: Whiteboard/virtual board architecture discussion
- **Pair Programming**: 30-minute collaborative coding session

#### Design Roles  
- **Portfolio Review**: 30-minute walkthrough of recent work
- **Design Challenge**: Create mockups for a given problem
- **Design Critique**: Review and improve existing designs
- **User Research**: Discussion of research methods and insights

#### Sales/Marketing Roles
- **Role Play**: Mock sales call or pitch presentation
- **Case Study**: Analyze and present marketing strategy
- **Metrics Discussion**: Experience with KPIs and analytics
- **Customer Scenarios**: How to handle difficult situations

